Matchmaking

In many cultures matchmaking and arrange marriages are common.

Today technology developments have advanced matchmaking to connect people with good matches.

According to Pew Research Center:

  • The general public perception towards online dating has become much more positive since 2005
  • One in ten Americans have used an online dating service themselves
  • Many people know someone using online dating, or who has found a spouse / long-term partner via online dating

Dataset:

  • Provided by Pew Research Center
  • Survey was completed in 2013 via telephone
  • 2,252 adults participated, 185 variables

Internet, Mobile, & Social Networking

The internet, along with mobile making it easier for us to access the internet, and trendy social networking sites, I wonder if online dating services are capturing all potential markets?

Conclusions:

  • 60% of singles looking for romance are currently not using Online Dating sites.

  • From this group it seems the target are adults who fall in the following groups:

  • Gender: Males
  • Age: Between the ages of 18-34
  • Education: With a H.S. Degree or less

  • Ethnicity: White American

Next Steps:

  • Analyze the main location of the target; is it a possible regional market?
  • Search for data released in the last year, compare the findings
  • Look for possible relationships between other variables
